StarHub’s First-Quarter Income Rises 62% to S$69.1 Million

-- B y   Y e e   K a i   P i n
-- 
2011-05-04T11:18:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/starhub-s-first-quarter-income-rises-62-to-s-69-1-million-1-.html
StarHub Ltd. (STH) , Singapore’s second-
largest phone company, reported a 62 percent rise in first-
quarter net profit as revenue increased from fixed-line and
mobile services.  StarHub posted a net profit of S$69.1 million, from S$42.7
million in the same quarter last year, according to a statement
today to the Singapore stock exchange. Revenue from fixed-
network services rose 4.6 percent, while revenue from mobile
services gained 3.3 percent.  Programming costs for pay-television businesses decreased,
the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yee Kai Pin in Singapore at 
